get.description: Get a list of all visible projects across GitLab for the authenticated user. When accessed without authentication, only public projects with simple fields are returned.

parameters.name: archived
parameters.description: Limit by archived status

parameters.name: id_after
parameters.description: Limit results to projects with IDs greater than the specified ID.

parameters.name: id_before
parameters.description: Limit results to projects with IDs less than the specified ID.

parameters.name: last_activity_after
parameters.description: Limit results to projects with last_activity after specified time.ISO 8601 YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ

parameters.name: last_activity_before
parameters.description: Limit results to projects with last_activity before specified time. ISO 8601 YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ

parameters.name: membership
parameters.description: Limit by projects that the current user is a member of.

parameters.name: min_access_level
parameters.description: Limit by current user minimal access level.

parameters.name: order_by
parameters.description: Return projects ordered by field

parameters.name: owned
parameters.description: Limit by projects explicitly owned by the current user.

parameters.name: repository_storage
parameters.description: Limit results to projects stored on repository_storage. (admins only)

parameters.name: search_namespaces
parameters.description: Include ancestor namespaces when matching search criteria.

parameters.name: search
parameters.description: Return list of projects matching the search criteria.

parameters.name: simple
parameters.description: Return only limited fields for each project. This is a no-op without authentication as then only simple fields are returned.

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: Return projects sorted in asc or desc order. Default is desc

parameters.name: starred
parameters.description: Limit by projects starred by the current user.

parameters.name: statistics
parameters.description: Include project statistics.

parameters.name: visibility
parameters.description: Limit by visibility

parameters.name: with_custom_attributes
parameters.description: Include custom attributes in response. (admins only)

parameters.name: with_issues_enabled
parameters.description: Limit by enabled issues feature.

parameters.name: with_merge_requests_enabled
parameters.description: Limit by enabled merge requests feature.

parameters.name: with_programming_language
parameters.description: Limit by projects which use the given programming language.

200.description: Get a projects list for authenticated user

post.description: Creates a new project owned by the authenticated user.

parameters.name: allow_merge_on_skipped_pipeline
parameters.description: Set whether or not merge requests can be merged with skipped jobs.

parameters.name: auto_cancel_pending_pipelines
parameters.description: Auto-cancel pending pipelines. This isn’t a boolean, but enabled/disabled.

parameters.name: auto_devops_deploy_strategy
parameters.description: Auto Deploy strategy

parameters.name: auto_devops_enabled
parameters.description: Enable Auto DevOps for this project.

parameters.name: autoclose_referenced_issues
parameters.description: Set whether auto-closing referenced issues on default branch.

parameters.name: avatar
parameters.description: Image file for avatar of the project.

parameters.name: build_coverage_regex
parameters.description: Test coverage parsing.

parameters.name: build_git_strategy
parameters.description: The Git strategy. Defaults to fetch.

parameters.name: build_timeout
parameters.description: The maximum amount of time in minutes that a job is able run (in seconds).

parameters.name: builds_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled, private, or enabled.

parameters.name: ci_config_path
parameters.description: The path to CI configuration file.

parameters.name: container_expiration_policy_attributes
parameters.description: Update the image cleanup policy for this project.

parameters.name: container_registry_enabled
parameters.description: Enable container registry for this project.

parameters.name: default_branch
parameters.description: master by default.

parameters.name: description
parameters.description: Short project description.

parameters.name: emails_disabled
parameters.description: Disable email notifications.

parameters.name: forking_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled,private, or enabled.

parameters.name: import_url
parameters.description: URL to import repository from. Either import_url or template_name is required, not both

parameters.name: initialize_with_readme
parameters.description: false by default.

parameters.name: issues_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled, private, or enabled.

parameters.name: issues_enabled
parameters.description: (Deprecated)Enable issues for this project. Use issues_access_level instead.

parameters.name: jobs_enabled
parameters.description: (Deprecated)Enable jobs for this project. Use builds_access_level instead.

parameters.name: lfs_enabled
parameters.description: Enable LFS.

parameters.name: merge_method
parameters.description: Set the merge method used.

parameters.name: merge_requests_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled, private, or enabled.

parameters.name: merge_requests_enabled
parameters.description: (Deprecated)Enable merge requests for this project. Use merge_requests_access_level instead.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the new project. Either path or name is required, not both.

parameters.name: namespace_id
parameters.description: Namespace for the new project (defaults to the current user's namespace).

parameters.name: only_allow_merge_if_all_discussions_are_resolved

parameters.name: only_allow_merge_if_pipeline_succeeds
parameters.description: Set whether merge requests can only be merged with successful jobs.

parameters.name: packages_enabled
parameters.description: Enable or disable packages repository feature.

parameters.name: pages_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled, private,enabled, or public.

parameters.name: requirements_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled,private,enabled or public

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: Repository name for new project. Generated based on name if not provided (generated as lowercase with dashes).

parameters.name: printing_merge_request_link_enabled
parameters.description: Show link to create/view merge request when pushing from the command line.

parameters.name: public_builds
parameters.description: If true, jobs can be viewed by non-project members.

parameters.name: remove_source_branch_after_merge
parameters.description: Enable Delete source branch option by default for all new merge requests.

parameters.name: repository_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled, private, or enabled.

parameters.name: repository_storage
parameters.description: Which storage shard the repository is on.(admins only)

parameters.name: request_access_enabled
parameters.description: Allow users to request member access.

parameters.name: resolve_outdated_diff_discussions
parameters.description: Automatically resolve merge request diffs discussions on lines changed with a push.

parameters.name: shared_runners_enabled
parameters.description: Enable shared runners for this project.

parameters.name: show_default_award_emojis
parameters.description: Show default award emojis.

parameters.name: snippets_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled, private, or enabled.

parameters.name: snippets_enabled
parameters.description: (Deprecated)Enable snippets for this project. Use snippets_access_level instead.

parameters.name: tag_list
parameters.description: The list of tags for a project; put array of tags, that should be finally assigned to a project.

parameters.name: template_name
parameters.description: When used withoutuse_custom_template, name of abuilt-in project template. When used withuse_custom_template, name of a custom project template.

parameters.name: visibility
parameters.description: See project visibility level.

parameters.name: wiki_access_level
parameters.description: One of disabled, private, or enabled.

parameters.name: wiki_enabled
parameters.description: (Deprecated)Enable wiki for this project. Use wiki_access_levelinstead.

get.description: Get all issues the authenticated user has access to. By default it returns only issues created by the current user. To get all issues, use parameter scope=all.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: Page number

parameters.name: per_page
parameters.description: Number of items to list per page

parameters.name: assignee_id
parameters.description: Return issues assigned to the given user id . Mutually exclusive with assignee_username . None returns unassigned issues. Any returns issues with an assignee. ( Introduced in GitLab 9.5)

parameters.name: assignee_username
parameters.description: Return issues assigned to the given username . Either assignee_username or assignee_id is required, not both. In GitLab CE, the assignee_username array should only contain a single value. Otherwise, an invalid parameter error is returned.

parameters.name: author_id
parameters.description: Return issues created by the given user id . Either author_id or author_username is required, not both. Combine with scope=all or scope=assigned_to_me . ( Introduced in GitLab 9.5)

parameters.name: author_username
parameters.description: Return issues created by the given username . Similar to author_id and mutually exclusive with author_id .

parameters.name: confidential
parameters.description: Filter confidential or public issues.

parameters.name: created_after
parameters.description: Return issues created on or after the given time. Expected in ISO 8601 format ( 2019-03-15T08:00:00Z )

parameters.name: created_before
parameters.description: Return issues created on or before the given time. Expected in ISO 8601 format ( 2019-03-15T08:00:00Z )

parameters.name: due_date
parameters.description: Return issues that have no due date, are overdue, or whose due date is this week, this month, or between two weeks ago and next month. Accepts: 0 (no due date), overdue , week , month , next_month_and_previous_two_weeks . (Introduced in GitLab 13.3 )

parameters.name: iids[]
parameters.description: Return only the issues having the given iid

parameters.name: in
parameters.description: Modify the scope of the search attribute. title , description , or a string joining them with comma. Default is title,description

parameters.name: milestone
parameters.description: The milestone title. None lists all issues with no milestone. Any lists all issues that have an assigned milestone.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: Comma-separated list of label names, issues must have all labels to be returned. None lists all issues with no labels. Any lists all issues with at least one label. No+Label (Deprecated) lists all issues with no labels. Predefined names are case-insensitive.

parameters.name: my_reaction_emoji
parameters.description: Return issues reacted by the authenticated user by the given emoji . None returns issues not given a reaction. Any returns issues given at least one reaction. ( Introduced in GitLab 10.0)

parameters.name: non_archived
parameters.description: Return issues only from non-archived projects. If false , the response returns issues from both archived and non-archived projects. Default is true . (Introduced in GitLab 13.0 )

parameters.name: not
parameters.description: Return issues that do not match the parameters supplied. Accepts: labels , milestone , author_id , author_username , assignee_id , assignee_username , my_reaction_emoji

parameters.name: order_by
parameters.description: Return issues ordered by created_at , updated_at , priority , due_date , relative_position , label_priority , milestone_due , popularity , weight fields. Default is created_at

parameters.name: scope
parameters.description: Return issues for the given scope: created_by_me , assigned_to_me or all . Defaults to created_by_me For versions before 11.0, use the now deprecated created-by-me or assigned-to-me scopes instead. ( Introduced in GitLab 9.5. Changed to snake_case in GitLab 11.0)

parameters.name: search
parameters.description: Search issues against their title and description

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: Return issues sorted in asc or desc order. Default is desc

parameters.name: state
parameters.description: Return all issues or just those that are opened or closed

parameters.name: updated_after
parameters.description: Return issues updated on or after the given time. Expected in ISO 8601 format ( 2019-03-15T08:00:00Z )

parameters.name: updated_before
parameters.description: Return issues updated on or before the given time. Expected in ISO 8601 format ( 2019-03-15T08:00:00Z )

parameters.name: with_labels_details
parameters.description: If true , the response returns more details for each label in labels field: :name , :color , :description , :description_html , :text_color . Default is false . The description_html attribute was introduced in GitLab 12.7

200.description: Get all issues the authenticated user has access to. By default it returns only issues created by the current user. To get all issues, use parameter scope=all.

get.description: Only for administrators. Get a single issue.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the issue

200.description: Only for administrators. Get a single issue.

get.description: Get a list of visible groups for the authenticated user. When accessed without authentication, only public groups are returned.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: Page number

parameters.name: per_page
parameters.description: Number of items to list per page

parameters.name: skip_groups
parameters.description: Skip the group IDs passed

parameters.name: all_available
parameters.description: Show all the groups you have access to (defaults tofalsefor authenticated users,truefor admin); Attributesownedandmin_access_levelhave precedence

parameters.name: search
parameters.description: Return the list of authorized groups matching the search criteria

parameters.name: order_by
parameters.description: Order groups byname,pathorid. Default is name

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: Order groups in asc or desc order. Default is asc

parameters.name: statistics
parameters.description: Include group statistics (admins only)

parameters.name: with_custom_attributes
parameters.description: Includecustom attributesin response (admins only)

parameters.name: owned
parameters.description: Limit to groups explicitly owned by the current user

parameters.name: min_access_level
parameters.description: Limit to groups where current user has at least this access level

parameters.name: top_level_only
parameters.description: Limit to top level groups, excluding all subgroups

200.description: Get a list of visible groups for the authenticated user. When accessed without authentication, only public groups are returned.

post.description: Creates a new project group. Available only for users who can create groups.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the group.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The path of the group.

parameters.name: description
parameters.description: The group's description.

parameters.name: visibility
parameters.description: The group's visibility. Can be private,internal, orpublic.

parameters.name: share_with_group_lock
parameters.description: Prevent sharing a project with another group within this group.

parameters.name: require_two_factor_authentication
parameters.description: Require all users in this group to setup Two-factor authentication.

parameters.name: two_factor_grace_period
parameters.description: Time before Two-factor authentication is enforced (in hours).

parameters.name: project_creation_level
parameters.description: Determine if developers can create projects in the group. Can benoone(No one),maintainer(Maintainers), or developer(Developers + Maintainers).

parameters.name: auto_devops_enabled
parameters.description: Default to Auto DevOps pipeline for all projects within this group.

parameters.name: subgroup_creation_level
parameters.description: Allowed to create subgroups. Can be owner(Owners), or maintainer(Maintainers).

parameters.name: emails_disabled
parameters.description: Disable email notifications

parameters.name: avatar
parameters.description: Image file for avatar of the group.Introduced in GitLab 12.9

parameters.name: mentions_disabled
parameters.description: Disable the capability of a group from getting mentioned

parameters.name: lfs_enabled
parameters.description: Enable/disable Large File Storage (LFS) for the projects in this group.

parameters.name: request_access_enabled
parameters.description: Allow users to request member access.

parameters.name: parent_id
parameters.description: The parent group ID for creating nested group.

parameters.name: default_branch_protection
parameters.description: SeeOptions fordefault_branch_protection. Default to the global level default branch protection setting.

parameters.name: shared_runners_setting
parameters.description: SeeOptions forshared_runners_setting. Enable or disable shared runners for a group’s subgroups and projects.
